translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: みんな、ふれてはいけない所にふれてしまったとあわてる
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Everyone panicked, realizing they touched a forbidden spot.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 気を取り直したコパンドン、
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Copandon pulled himself together,

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 木のオーブ、ここから南にある闘神都市にあるねん。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The wooden orb is in the Fighting God City, located south from here.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 魔剣カオスが突き刺さっている台座の裏側に隠されているよ
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: It's hidden behind the pedestal where the demon sword Chaos is stuck.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 夜
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Night.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: その日はＭランドで遊んだ。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: They spent that day playing at M-Land.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 楽しかったねとか少し話・・
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: They talked a bit about how fun it was...

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: で、闘神都市の話題になる
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Then the topic turned to the Fighting God City.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 闘神都市、今　闘神大会が開かれている都市
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The Fighting God City, where the Fighting God Tournament is currently being held.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 魔剣カオスは聖刀日光と共に唯一の魔王、魔人を倒せる武器
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The demon sword Chaos, along with the holy sword Nikkou, is one of the only weapons capable of defeating demon kings and demons.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 元は魔王ランスが持っていた武器だったが、魔王になった後は手放し
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Originally, it was a weapon wielded by Demon King Rance, but after becoming the demon king, he let it go.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: カーマが持ち主になり魔王ランスに挑んだが破れ、カオスは魔王により
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Karma became its owner and challenged Demon King Rance but was defeated, and Chaos was by the demon king

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 遠くへ放り投げられ岩に突き刺さった
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: thrown far away and stuck into a rock.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: この魔剣カオスが突き刺さった岩は有名となり、みなが引き抜こうとしてチャレンジした
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The rock where the demon sword Chaos is stuck became famous, and many tried to challenge themselves by pulling it out.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: そのうち、これを闘神都市が岩毎買い取って闘神大会の副賞にした
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Eventually, the Fighting God City purchased the entire rock and made it a secondary prize of the Fighting God Tournament.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 闘神大会本戦出場者が引き抜くチャレンジが出来るようになっている
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Contestants in the main tournament can challenge themselves to pull it out.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 今はまだ誰も引き抜けていない
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: So far, no one has been able to pull it out.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 木のオーブはこのカオスが刺さった岩の土台にあるそうだ。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The wooden orb is said to be at the base of the rock where Chaos is stuck.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 闘神大会本戦に出場して、カオスを抜く権利を得るのがよいな。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: It would be good to enter the main tournament to earn the right to pull out Chaos.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ちょうど、来週から今年の闘神大会が開かれるそうだ
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Apparently, this year's Fighting God Tournament starts next week.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: さっそく行こう
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Let's go right away.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: エール達は闘神都市に到着した。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Eiru and the others arrived at the Fighting God City.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 都市は大会を前に賑わっている、お祭り騒ぎ
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The city was bustling before the tournament, like a festival.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: さっそく事務局にいって手続きをしようと行くと
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: They immediately went to the office to proceed with the registration.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 事務員さん（シュリさん）と男が揉めている
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The clerk (Shuri-san) and a man were having a quarrel.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 「なんで駄目なんだよ、こんな美人なのにお前の目は節穴か？」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: "Why is it no good? She's such a beauty—are your eyes blind?"

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 「レイ、どうしても参加したいのなら、別に私じゃなくて誰か別の人を雇ってパートナーにしたら？」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: "Rei, if you really want to participate, why don't you hire someone else as your partner instead of me?"

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 「ばかやろう、俺のパートナーはお前だけなんだよ」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: "You idiot, you're the only partner I have."

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 「もういい、また来年来る」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: "Fine, I'll come again next year."

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: と出て行く
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: And he left.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 今の人、魔人レイじゃないのか・・
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: That guy just now, isn't he the demon Rei...?

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: いや、まさか・・そんな、似た人でしょ
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: No, no way... he must be someone who just looks like him.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: レイを知っているのは、リセット、ザンス、ロッキー、レリコフ、など、けっこうみんな知っているはず
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Those who know Rei include Reset, Zans, Rocky, Lericov, and quite a few others should know him.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: まぁ、それはさておいてエール達も事務局に入る
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Well, putting that aside, Eiru and the others also entered the office.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: シュリさんが出てくる、闘神大会の説明を聞く
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Shuri-san came out, and they listened to an explanation about the Fighting God Tournament.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 『闘神大会ルール』
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: "Fighting God Tournament Rules"

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 闘神大会は、闘神都市で毎年おこなわれている戦士どうしの
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The Fighting God Tournament is an annual competition held in the Fighting God City between warriors.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: トーナメント形式の大会である
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: It is a tournament-style competition.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 【闘神大会の出場資格】
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: [Eligibility for the Fighting God Tournament]

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: １：Ｌｖ３０以上、ある程度の戦闘力のある事
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: 1: Level 30 or above and some degree of combat ability.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ２：美しい女性のパートナーがいること
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: 2: Must have a beautiful female partner.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: （本人が女性の場合はパートナーを兼ねることも可）
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: (If the participant is female, she may also act as her own partner.)

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 【本戦出場の報償】
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: [Rewards for main tournament participation]

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: １：賞金１０００Ｇｏｌｄと記念バッチ
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: 1: Prize money of 1000 Gold and a commemorative badge.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ２：魔剣カオス引き抜きチャレンジ権
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: 2: The right to challenge pulling out the demon sword Chaos.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 【一試合勝つことの褒賞】
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: [Rewards for winning a match]

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: １：相手のパートナーを一晩自由にできる権利
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: 1: The right to freely spend a night with the opponent’s partner.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ２：賞金１万Ｇｏｌｄと宝物
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: 2: Prize money of 10,000 Gold and treasures.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 【優勝した時の褒賞】
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: [Rewards for winning the championship]

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: １：将軍の地位がもらえる
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: 1: You receive the position of general.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ２：闘神の館でパートナーと共に生涯何不自由なく暮らせる
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: 2: You can live comfortably for life with your partner in the Fighting God Mansion.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ３：ＧｏｌｄＣａｒｄを貰える
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: 3: You receive a Gold Card.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ４：賞金１００万Ｇｏｌｄと宝物
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: 4: Prize money of 1,000,000 Gold and treasures.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 【試合のルール】
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: [Match Rules]

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ・闘神大会の試合は一対一の対決
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: - Matches in the Fighting God Tournament are one-on-one duels.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ・武器は個人で携帯できる範囲で可能
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: - Weapons allowed are those that can be personally carried.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ・勝敗は相手が死ぬか降伏した時に決定する
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: - Victory is decided when the opponent dies or surrenders.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: みんな、ふれてはいけない所にふれてしまったとあわてる
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Everyone panicked, realizing they touched a forbidden spot.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 気を取り直したコパンドン、
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Copandon pulled himself together,

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 木のオーブ、ここから南にある闘神都市にあるねん。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The wooden orb is in the Fighting God City, located south from here.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 魔剣カオスが突き刺さっている台座の裏側に隠されているよ
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: It's hidden behind the pedestal where the demon sword Chaos is stuck.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 夜
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Night.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: その日はＭランドで遊んだ。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: They spent that day playing at M-Land.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 楽しかったねとか少し話・・
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: They talked a bit about how fun it was...

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: で、闘神都市の話題になる
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Then the topic turned to the Fighting God City.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 闘神都市、今　闘神大会が開かれている都市
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The Fighting God City, where the Fighting God Tournament is currently being held.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 魔剣カオスは聖刀日光と共に唯一の魔王、魔人を倒せる武器
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The demon sword Chaos, along with the holy sword Nikkou, is one of the only weapons capable of defeating demon kings and demons.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 元は魔王ランスが持っていた武器だったが、魔王になった後は手放し
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Originally, it was a weapon wielded by Demon King Rance, but after becoming the demon king, he let it go.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: カーマが持ち主になり魔王ランスに挑んだが破れ、カオスは魔王により
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Karma became its owner and challenged Demon King Rance but was defeated, and Chaos was by the demon king

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 遠くへ放り投げられ岩に突き刺さった
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: thrown far away and stuck into a rock.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: この魔剣カオスが突き刺さった岩は有名となり、みなが引き抜こうとしてチャレンジした
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The rock where the demon sword Chaos is stuck became famous, and many tried to challenge themselves by pulling it out.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: そのうち、これを闘神都市が岩毎買い取って闘神大会の副賞にした
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Eventually, the Fighting God City purchased the entire rock and made it a secondary prize of the Fighting God Tournament.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 闘神大会本戦出場者が引き抜くチャレンジが出来るようになっている
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Contestants in the main tournament can challenge themselves to pull it out.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 今はまだ誰も引き抜けていない
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: So far, no one has been able to pull it out.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 木のオーブはこのカオスが刺さった岩の土台にあるそうだ。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The wooden orb is said to be at the base of the rock where Chaos is stuck.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 闘神大会本戦に出場して、カオスを抜く権利を得るのがよいな。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: It would be good to enter the main tournament to earn the right to pull out Chaos.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ちょうど、来週から今年の闘神大会が開かれるそうだ
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Apparently, this year's Fighting God Tournament starts next week.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: さっそく行こう
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Let's go right away.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: エール達は闘神都市に到着した。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Eiru and the others arrived at the Fighting God City.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 都市は大会を前に賑わっている、お祭り騒ぎ
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The city was bustling before the tournament, like a festival.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: さっそく事務局にいって手続きをしようと行くと
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: They immediately went to the office to proceed with the registration.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 事務員さん（シュリさん）と男が揉めている
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The clerk (Shuri-san) and a man were having a quarrel.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 「なんで駄目なんだよ、こんな美人なのにお前の目は節穴か？」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: "Why is it no good? She's such a beauty—are your eyes blind?"

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 「レイ、どうしても参加したいのなら、別に私じゃなくて誰か別の人を雇ってパートナーにしたら？」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: "Rei, if you really want to participate, why don't you hire someone else as your partner instead of me?"

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 「ばかやろう、俺のパートナーはお前だけなんだよ」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: "You idiot, you're the only partner I have."

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 「もういい、また来年来る」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: "Fine, I'll come again next year."

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: と出て行く
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: And he left.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 今の人、魔人レイじゃないのか・・
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: That guy just now, isn't he the demon Rei...?

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: いや、まさか・・そんな、似た人でしょ
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: No, no way... he must be someone who just looks like him.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: レイを知っているのは、リセット、ザンス、ロッキー、レリコフ、など、けっこうみんな知っているはず
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Those who know Rei include Reset, Zans, Rocky, Lericov, and quite a few others should know him.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: まぁ、それはさておいてエール達も事務局に入る
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Well, putting that aside, Eiru and the others also entered the office.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: シュリさんが出てくる、闘神大会の説明を聞く
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Shuri-san came out, and they listened to an explanation about the Fighting God Tournament.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 『闘神大会ルール』
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: "Fighting God Tournament Rules"

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 闘神大会は、闘神都市で毎年おこなわれている戦士どうしの
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The Fighting God Tournament is an annual competition held in the Fighting God City between warriors.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: トーナメント形式の大会である
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: It is a tournament-style competition.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 【闘神大会の出場資格】
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: [Eligibility for the Fighting God Tournament]

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: １：Ｌｖ３０以上、ある程度の戦闘力のある事
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: 1: Level 30 or above and some degree of combat ability.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ２：美しい女性のパートナーがいること
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: 2: Must have a beautiful female partner.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: （本人が女性の場合はパートナーを兼ねることも可）
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: (If the participant is female, she may also act as her own partner.)

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 【本戦出場の報償】
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: [Rewards for main tournament participation]

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: １：賞金１０００Ｇｏｌｄと記念バッチ
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: 1: Prize money of 1000 Gold and a commemorative badge.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ２：魔剣カオス引き抜きチャレンジ権
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: 2: The right to challenge pulling out the demon sword Chaos.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 【一試合勝つことの褒賞】
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: [Rewards for winning a match]

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: １：相手のパートナーを一晩自由にできる権利
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: 1: The right to freely spend a night with the opponent’s partner.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ２：賞金１万Ｇｏｌｄと宝物
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: 2: Prize money of 10,000 Gold and treasures.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 【優勝した時の褒賞】
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: [Rewards for winning the championship]

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: １：将軍の地位がもらえる
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: 1: You receive the position of general.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ２：闘神の館でパートナーと共に生涯何不自由なく暮らせる
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: 2: You can live comfortably for life with your partner in the Fighting God Mansion.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ３：ＧｏｌｄＣａｒｄを貰える
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: 3: You receive a Gold Card.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ４：賞金１００万Ｇｏｌｄと宝物
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: 4: Prize money of 1,000,000 Gold and treasures.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 【試合のルール】
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: [Match Rules]

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ・闘神大会の試合は一対一の対決
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: - Matches in the Fighting God Tournament are one-on-one duels.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ・武器は個人で携帯できる範囲で可能
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: - Weapons allowed are those that can be personally carried.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ・勝敗は相手が死ぬか降伏した時に決定する
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: - Victory is decided when the opponent dies or surrenders.
